metadata.name: Tamashi
metadata.description: Nephew of Satoshi, the founder of the first blockchain coin and the first multidimensional traveller, Tamashi was just a teenager when he discovered his family’s fight against the Multisolar Corporations. His journey made him the greatest human Ninja and brought him in possession of the legendary X, Y and Z blades, keys to travelling through the multiverse and break the “Walled Gardens”, barriers put by the Multisolar Corporations to limit multidimensional travel. But his sense of humor stayed the same - luckily or not, it depends on who you ask.

lore.short: Nephew of Satoshi, the founder of the first blockchain coin and the first multidimensional traveller, Tamashi was just a teenager when he discovered his family’s fight against the Multisolar Corporations. His journey made him the greatest human Ninja and brought him in possession of the legendary X, Y and Z blades, keys to travelling through the multiverse and break the “Walled Gardens”, barriers put by the Multisolar Corporations to limit multidimensional travel. But his sense of humor stayed the same - luckily or not, it depends on who you ask.
lore.long: He’d always dreamt of something more while living on the most beautiful archipelagos of the Atlantic. But little did he know that the tales of ancient dragons and alternate realities he’d heard from an old village were far from mere fantasy. And he would come to understand not only that he was adopted, but that his very biological father, Ayumu, son of Satoshi Nakomoto, was playing a role in what was the most important confrontation of human history: the fight against those that quietly enslaved civilizations. Those that were responsible for the death of his mother, and now the disappearance of his real father. Desperate for answers, when he discovered his father’s research, he finally jumped between universes for the first time, only to come back to and find his own girlfriend missing. It was obvious that he had been observed by what his father’s memoirs called “Multisolar Corporations”, and now, it got personal. But no one, not even Caleidon, predicted that Tamashi would be able to escape them and find the X,Y and Z blades. Now he just had to actually take them…
